If ya did not know I will be arriving back in Seattle around the 11th of August. I will most likely be crashing at Connors or Kellys for a week till i can get stuff situated and get the job hunt rolling. Not making any promises as to how long i will be staying in Seattle, alot depends on how things go the first week. I may just decide its been nice, say hi to everyone and then leave again. We will see...


Until then, stock up on the nuggage and the beers... its going to be an interesting first week back, to say the least.

I think the life cycle is backwards: 
You should die first, start out dead and get it out of the way. 
Then you wake up in an old age home, feeling better every day. 
You get kicked out for being too healthy, go collect your pension, 
then, when you start work, you get a gold watch on your first day. 
You work 40 years until you're young enough to enjoy your retirement. 
You drink alcohol, you party, you're generally promiscuous and  you 
get ready for High School. 
You go to primary school, you become a kid, you play, you have no 
responsibilities, you become a baby, then, you spend your last 9 
months floating peacefully with luxuries like central heating, spa, room 
service on tap, larger quarters everyday, and finally you finish  off 
as an orgasm. 

I rest my case.  :)

Well after a 30+ hour bus ride i am finally at my Dads house for a bit, I am seriously thinking of going down to Mississippi or New Orleans to do some volunteering for a bit. I am sure all of you have seen news coverage but believe me when i say that what ever you have seen in the papers or on TV is nothing compared to the reality of the situation down there. Saw a picture today in the local paper of a casino that had been pushed 500ft off its foundation. Now this is not a small building and to see where it was and where it is now was pretty crazy. Also any of you that can help please do so, money, canned food, phone cards, prepaid cellphones/cell minute cards, anything. 

Ok thats enough of that. Depending on what happens in the next week i should be back in Seattle around the middle of Oct. Got some more traveling to do before i head back regardless of whether or not i go down to help out.

well its been four months since I left Washington and came to Maine. Time for another change of venue. Will probly end up doing a Greyhound tour of the country to visit relatives on this coast while i am here. Been an interesting four months to say the least, spent the first three months trying to overdoase my liver and the last one trying to recouperate it before i head back into the rest of humanity. I have to say that the hardest thing to get over when i leave here will be engaging in the Maine state sport... What is the Maine State sport u are asking... well in usually involves a case or two of cheap beer of a bottle of "Hick Juice" aka Allens Coffee Brandy and a car... yep drunken driving seems to be what most of these hillbillies do for fun out here... well for those of u who care i should be back in Washington around the end of Sept or early Oct.

Peace out for now

If i was a serial killer i would be The Zodiac Killer.

Over the course of almost 9 years in the 1970s the Zodiac Killer took the lives of over 13 people, either stabbing or shooting them to death in or by their vehicles. All the targets were the same, couples in cars off rural roads.

Taunting cops the Zodiac Killer would send in encrypted messages to the local papers, describing how his past victims had died, and who would come next if they didn't post his message on the cover of the newspaper the following day. The only surviving witness described the zodiac killer as a heavy set man in a self fashioned hooded jacked that covered his face, brandishing a crossed circle that he always signed his letters with.

After 1978 the killings stopped, the Zodiac's case was never solved.

Kill count: 13

Seems that I have not given up the age old habit of burning my bridges before i cross them. I managed to royally piss off the only person i truely care about anymore. Said some stuff that i probly shouldnt have said but i feel none the less, and unfortunately I'm sorry isnt going to cut it this time. So i am going to take this time to formally announce that i am moving out of state in the next few months and will probly not be coming back any time soon. To all my friends who may happen to read this, it has been interesting times to say the least, to those who dont read this, well i am sure you will find out sometime soon. Oh... my kingdom... my kingdom for some prozium... opiate of the masses.

to the love of my life, i would like to say that i am truely sorry, and that if i could take back the things i said i would, but it wont make me feel them any less. I do truely wish you well and hope that you some day find what you are looking for, Bob knows i dont think i ever will.

You are the Moon card. Entering the Moon we enter
the intuitive and psychic realms. This is the
stuff dreams are made on. And like dreams the
imagery we find here may inspire us or torment
us. Understanding the moon requires looking
within. Our own bodily rhythms are echoed in
this luminary that circles the earth every
month and reflects the sun in its progress.
Listening to those rhythms may produce visions
and lead you towards insight. The Moon is a
force that has legends attached to it. It
carries with it both romance and insanity.
Moonlight reveals itself as an illusion and it
is only those willing to work with the force of
dreams that are able to withstand this
reflective light. Image from: Stevee Postman.

Man i really need to stop drinking before i go to bed. the dreams are interesting to be sure but i have enough emotional shit to deal with when i am awake dont need my subconscious joining in on the party. I mean really I almost felt worse waking up than when i finally passed out. of course that could just be the hangover but i doubt it.

well ride is here so i am off to MarioLand...

Not sure why i am even doing this... but sometimes u just have to go with that gutt feeling. Well I really cannot wait for this fucking year to be over. Man what a year. My best friend is thrown in jail on a bogus child molestation charge, his rotten cunt of a girl friend gets me fired. a very good friend of mine decides that it is time to check out and hangs himself. There are times when i want to ask myself whats the point? BUT when you start asking questions like that you want to answer them, when you can find the answers you just get more frustrated. God i want my life to be simple again. I have to say that if it wasnt for a few very close friends i would have probably gone on to the planet Arcturus by now. I mean fuck... i just want off this rock one way or another. 

ok now that that is out of my system and i have a few shots in me... I get to rejoin the work force on Tuesday. yay me. I get every kids dream job. Playtesting video games. WEEEEEEEEE but hey its a job and it pays the bills. eat breathe shit repeat...

ok I am done for the night... to anyone who reads this shit... I am sorry... ya coulda been doing something entertaining.
